
# Day 02 - Linux Server Health Checker

## Objective
Create a Bash script to monitor the health of a Linux server.

## Features
- Display hostname
- Display current user
- Display current date and time
- Show disk usage
- Show memory usage
- Show system uptime

## Technologies
- Ubuntu (WSL)
- Bash
- Git
- GitHub

## Run

```bash
chmod +x health-check.sh
./health-check.sh
```

## Sample Output

```
Hostname: LAPTOP-F82KK5UE
Current User: sunil
Disk Usage...
Memory Usage...
```

## What I Learned

- Bash scripting
- Linux commands
- File permissions using chmod
- Executing shell scripts
- Basic server monitoring
